Based on my analysis of the code and the test case, I believe the issue is in the `guessX` method where division by very small numbers can occur, causing numerical instability. Let me look more carefully at the Newton interpolation in the `guessX` method:

The issue occurs in this section of `guessX`:
```java
for (int i = start; i < end - 1; ++i) {
    final int delta = i + 1 - start;
    for (int j = end - 1; j > i; --j) {
        x[j] = (x[j] - x[j-1]) / (y[j] - y[j - delta]);
    }
}
```

When `y[j] - y[j - delta]` is very close to zero, this causes numerical instability. The fix should add a check to detect when the denominator is too small and handle it appropriately.

Let me fix the issue:

